    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Words We Understand</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Janice Gewirtz letter scores Pres Bush for continuing to use word 'victory' in connection with Iraq because he does not want to look as if he is changing his policy (Jan 2 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Chaos Overran Iraq Plan in '06, Bush Team Says'' (front page, Jan. 2):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Chaos Overran Iraq Plan in '06, Bush Team Says'' (front page, Jan. 2):</p>
        <p>It is galling and condescending that President Bush keeps talking about victory in Iraq. ''It's a word the American people understand,'' he told members of the Iraq Study Group. ''And if I start to change it, it will look like I'm beginning to change my policy.''</p>
        <p>Americans also understand the word ''failure,'' and having seen it in Iraq, voted resoundingly for a change in policy in November.</p>
        <p>Janice Gewirtz  Mountain Lakes, N.J., Jan. 2, 2007</p>
      </block>
